Commentary Text: Unadkat to Shami, out Caught by Stokes!! That's a superb catch from Stokes - he hasn't just saved a six, but he has got Unadkat a wicket as well. Watches the ball all the way at the deep mid-wicket boundary, lunges behind, holds onto the overhead catch - realises that he was going over the ropes, chucks the ball back into play, crosses the ropes, comes back in and takes the catch. Coming to the ball, it was a length delivery on the stumps, Shami backed away and swung hard - looked like he had got plenty behind it - only for Stokes to spoil his party. Shami c Stokes b Unadkat 2(4)

Commentary Text: Washington Sundar to Corey Anderson, out Stumped!! Dhoni is confident about a stumping. When he's confident, it means he's got his man. Looks like Anderson's foot is in the air, he did well to drag back in, but couldn't get his feet down. OUT is the call. Excellent work from MS, quick hands did the trick, but that was very well bowled by Sundar as well. He slowed down the pace, dragged Anderson forward on the drive and did him in with the turn. Commentary Text: Christian to Samuels, out Caught by Dhoni!! 101st dismissal for MS and he took it as cool as a cucumber. He's still one of the best keepers in the game - and this catch shows why. This was another slower short ball from Christian, Samuels made room outside leg and was looking to flay it through mid-wicket, played the shot a tad too early, got a fat top-edge. For a moment he seemed to be safe, but there was that man. MS ran backwards, kept his eyes on the ball, timed his leap well and completed a one-handed catch - with his right glove. Christian clenches his fists in delight - as much as a keeper's wicket as it was for the bowler there. Samuels c Dhoni b Christian 27(21) [4s-1 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Shami to Stokes, out Caught by Corey Anderson!! Shami misses the blockhole and delivers a full toss, Stokes advances and converts it into a slightly higher full toss than he would have liked. It takes him by surprise a bit. He swings hard, it hits him high on the bat and he ends up slicing it straight down to long-off. Had he stayed his ground, would have been a much simpler ball to hit.
